      <item>
        <title>Recuperando o GRUB</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Quando você faz a instalação do Ubuntu usando &lt;strong&gt;dual boot&lt;/strong&gt;…&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Instale primeiro o Windows&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Depois instale o Ubuntu&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;… você terá uma tela parecida com essa. O famoso &lt;strong&gt;GRUB&lt;/strong&gt;, onde você escolhe qual SO você quer inicializar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/img/posts/post-bg-grub.png&quot; alt=&quot;post-bg-grub.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mas e no dia que dá pau no computador e você não consegue inicializar o GRUB? Calma, não precisa se desesperar e jogar o computador no lixo.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Faça o seguinte:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Inicie um &lt;strong&gt;Live-CD&lt;/strong&gt; ou &lt;strong&gt;Live-USB&lt;/strong&gt; com a mesma arquitetura do Linux que estava instalado, ou seja, se o Linux instalado for 64 Bits, use Live-CD ou Live-USB 64bits, se o Linux instalado for 32bits use Live-CD ou Live-USB 32bits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Abra o &lt;strong&gt;terminal&lt;/strong&gt; (CTRL+ALT+T)&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;e digite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;sudo su&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Veja qual partição está instalada o seu Linux&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;lsblk&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/img/posts/lsblk.png&quot; alt=&quot;lsblk.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Crie uma pasta para ser o ponto de montagem&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;mkdir hd&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Monte a partição que tem o Linux&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;mount /dev/sda3 hd/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nota:&lt;/strong&gt; no meu caso &lt;em&gt;sda3&lt;/em&gt; é a minha partição Linux, talvez na sua seja diferente.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Vincule temporariamente os dispositivos e processos ativados atualmente pelo Live-CD no Linux que está instalado.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;mount --bind /dev/ hd/dev
mount --bind /proc/ hd/proc
mount --bind /sys/ hd/sys&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mude temporariamente a referência ao &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;/&lt;/code&gt; para dentro da pasta&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;chroot hd/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reinstale o GRUB utilizando o próprio sistema instalado no hd&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;grub-install /dev/sda
update-grub
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;exit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Desmonte todas as partições&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;umount -a&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reinicie o sistema&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;reboot&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Agradecimentos ao meu amigo &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/luzfcb/69ed9391290952a1f881&quot;&gt;Fábio&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
